Description
-----------
-Program takes command line arguments from main.ko module.
-Adds using add.ko module that exports symbol so that it can be called from driver program.

Steps for compilation
---------------------
1.a)make 
  To generate kernel modules.

Or,

  b)make modules 
  To generate kernel modules.

Note: Check module parameters to be passed using: modinfo main.ko
-----

2. insmod add.ko main.ko a=10 b=20
   To insert .ko modules along with command line arguments.

3. rmmod main add
   To remove .ko modules.

4. make clean
To remove .ko file.

Note: Run dmesg : To see log messages.

Output
------

1) When module is inserted.
[81881.848623] add_init :
[81881.848623]  <6>[81889.336423] main_init : add=30


2) When module is removed.
[81904.776040] main_exit : Bye bye
[81904.776337] 
[81904.776337] add_exit : Bye bye





